<plot>Benny Gopher leaves his home in the country to make it big in Hollywood. When he arrives in Tinsel Town he finds the only job open to him is to be a gopher to superstar Cary Ant. Benny joins Cary on the lot of "Sunshine Pictures - Hollywood's Brightest Studio!" There he meets Arnold Hamandegger, Charlie Chimplin, Jay Rhino, Gloria Swansong, Frankie Sinatrat and the rest of the Rat Pack, and other show business greats. While lost on the lot, Benny stumbles across the office of Louie B. Mole head of the studio. Benny pitches Louie an idea for a movie called "Sunshine Boulevard." We follow Benny's imagination during this parody of the classic film. Soon, Benny learns that even if it means slowing down his career, being truthful with one self and others is the best way to go.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?378999</url></doc>
